Package xland.mcmod.enchlevellangpatch.api

Interface EnchantmentLevelLangPatch

Functional Interface:
This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.
@API(status=STABLE) @FunctionalInterface public interface EnchantmentLevelLangPatch
An API to patch the language file of Minecraft, resource packs and mods.

    • registerEnchantmentPatch

      static void registerEnchantmentPatch(@NotNull @NotNull String id, @NotNull @NotNull EnchantmentLevelLangPatch edition)

      Register an extra rendering syntax for enchantment levels.

      Won't be applied without invoking EnchantmentLevelLangPatchConfig.setCurrentEnchantmentHooks(xland.mcmod.enchlevellangpatch.api.EnchantmentLevelLangPatch), which switches the enchantment level patch to whichever you want.

      Parameters:
      id - Namespaced key for your patch. Please follow the naming rule of namespaced keys.
      edition - Your patch for enchantment levels.
      See Also:
      • EnchantmentLevelLangPatchConfig.setCurrentEnchantmentHooks(xland.mcmod.enchlevellangpatch.api.EnchantmentLevelLangPatch)
